title: Act1_Introduction
---
<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Twenty-two Arcana shape the world,[/i]
: [i]each a guiding star of fate.[/i]
: [i]Their ideals collide through mortal hands,[/i]
: [i]and in that clash of faith and will,[/i]
: [i]balance is born.[/i]
: [i]But one, the Hierophant, tipped these scales in their pursuit of absolute order, a world where all beings would be under his control. It is here where your mission begins.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
???: Hello? 
???: Hhhheeelllooo!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
???: ...

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
???: Oh! You’re finally awake.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
???: ???

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
???: Alright, let’s do this slowly.
???: Name. Do you remember that much?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
???: [i]My name? It’s...[/i]
Cyrus: Cyrus.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
???: Great! At least part of your brain still works, that’s better than some. You can call me the Judge.
The Judge: So! Cyrus! You’re an enforcer of the Almighty Justice, chosen to preserve fairness and law throughout the universe.
The Judge: It’s an honor few humans receive, but to keep your work professional we can’t have you keeping memories.
The Judge: Your next mission will be in Prism.
The Judge: The Hierophant’s been tampering with the divine balance, and your job is to hunt down his puppets before he uses them to bring the Assimilation.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: What? What are you you even-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: Look, you want humanity to continue, right? So do we.
The Judge: Well, Justice does. I just work here.
The Judge: So I’d love to stand here and explain the metaphysics of divine politics, but we’re really on a schedule. Off you go!

<<player_respawn YarnManager>>
===


title: Act1_EveIntro_PreCombat_P1N1
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
???: Oh good, you’re awake!
???: Ah! Sorry, I didn’t mean to scare you.
???: I found you on the outskirts and brought you here. We should be safe for now.
Eve: I’m Eve. I don’t think I’ve seen you around this part of town. What’s your name?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: ...
Cyrus: This is the second time I’ve woken up in five minutes.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: What?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Sorry, I’m just...right, my name. It’s Cyrus.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Nice to meet you, Cyrus! Or not nice? Given the circumstances. Are you hurt anywhere?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]What’s happening? That girl earlier... I can’t seem to remember anything beyond my own name. Best to play along for now.[/i]

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]An inhuman roar. (TODO play sound)[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: That’s not good. Sounds like a Meminiscor.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: What is that?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You don’t know?
Eve: They’re drawn to strong emotions, that must’ve been how they found us.
Eve: We have to go-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Get down!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Thanks! Uh-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Do you have a weapon?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: A gun, but I’m not-
 
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’ll take it.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Be careful! If you get too close, it’ll start absorbing your memories.
===


title: Act1_EveIntro_PostCombat_P1N1
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Where did I learn to do that?[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You actually did it. Are you a Hunter?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Hunter?

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]A distant roar is heard. (TODO play sound)[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: We’d better head back to the city.
===


