title: Act1_EveWorldbuilding_P1N2
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You really aren’t from around here, are you?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’m not sure where I’m from.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: So you have the skills of a Hunter but remember nothing...maybe you exchanged your Fates away?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Fates?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Strong memories, the kind that only happens a few times in a person’s life.
Eve: Depending on the memory and what Arcana it’s aligned with, they’ll each grant you a unique power. Tell me you at least know what an Arcana is.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I remember, uh, Justice?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Good. Say you became a judge to ensure fair rulings in court. That Fate would be tied to the Justice Arcana, which may then grant you stronger defense.
Eve: Throughout life, we gain many Fates from different Arcanas. 
Eve: You can trade them like any other currency, but if you lose them all you’ll become one of those things we ran into.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Memory monsters...that’s how they get their name.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: They didn’t make the warmest welcome, but, luckily we have Hunters to fight them off.
Eve: I’m surprised you aren’t one already. You can make a lot of money hunting those things.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Hunting...isn’t that what the Judge said to do?[/i]
Cyrus: How do I start?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Well, you'll need a dispatcher to guide you over the air. Which should be me.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: You sound eager.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Our town would be a lot safer with a Hunter like you.
Eve: And I’ll get a cut of your profits, of course.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: So [i]that's[/i] your motive.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Haha, yep~ You’ll need better equipment if you want to survive your first day. The shop’s up ahead.
===


title: Act1_ShopIntro_P1N5
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: Eve? Where have you been?!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Had a run-in with some monsters, but we handled it.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: You have a habit of getting yourself in danger the moment I turn my- Who’s this?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Oh! Dad, this is Cyrus. He’s a Hunter- well, a Hunter-in-training.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: A Hunter, eh? My shop here has the best supplies you’ll find in this town.
Shopkeeper: For a friend of my daughter’s I’ll even throw in a discount.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Thanks. Guess I’ll be lucky to have her as a dispatcher.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: Eve???

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: I-I’m just helping from the radio, I won’t be on the ground!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: What have I told you about-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: I’ll be safe, Dad, I promise!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: ...I can’t believe you.
Shopkeeper: Well, Cyrus. You ought to take a look at my wares. Don’t want you getting killed either.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Cyrus and Shopkeeper enter the shop.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: Here, I’ve got all the Fates a Hunter could ask for.

<<open_shop YarnManager>>
<<wait_for_shop_close YarnManager>>

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Huh? This photo...

<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: My daughters.
Shopkeeper: This one is Ava. She was the brightest kid you’d ever meet, you could tell even when she was a baby.
Shopkeeper: And that one’s Eve, of course. She showed up at the door one night a few years back, looking up at me like a lost puppy. Really brings back memories.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Cyrus leaves the shop.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Now you look like a real Hunter! I got you registered while you were in there.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: It’s that easy? No paperwork?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Thankfully not, they’re too desperate for new Hunters.

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]Eve’s device dings.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: That was fast.
Eve: Your first mission’s already here, they’re sending you deeper into the outskirts. Let’s head out.
===


title: Act1_TownProtection_PreCombat_P1N8
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: I should’ve warned you about Dad. He’s always been overprotective, but ever since the Assimilation started picking up...

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]The Assimilation. The Judge mentioned that.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Oh, right, you probably don’t know. Once the memory monsters have consumed enough memories, the Assimilation ritual will begin and humanity’s memories will be completely swallowed up.
Eve: We’ve always known it would happen one day, but it’ll be sooner than we thought.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: So the world is facing inevitable destruction? That’s terrible.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Not the best place to wake up in, huh?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: What about the other Arcanas, then? If they preside over this world, shouldn’t they do something about its destruction?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: They’re not saviors or destroyers, they only seek to enforce their principles. They can’t even interfere directly with this world.
Eve: But you’re right. Perhaps certain Arcanas have already directed their followers to oppose it.
Eve: I’m picking up memory monsters up ahead. There’s been a lot more around here lately.
Eve: I’ll guide you through. Just don’t get yourself killed on your first run, okay?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’ll try my best.
===


title: Act1_TownProtection_PostCombat_P1N8
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: That’s almost all of them. 
Cyrus: Eve, status?
Cyrus: ...Eve?
Cyrus: [i]Line’s dead. I need to get back, fast.[/i]
===


