title: FirstResurrection
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: ...
Cyrus: Did I...die?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: Don’t take it too hard. Most enforcers fail their first run. And their second. And, well...you’ll see.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: The monster, the pain- I felt it. How am I still here?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: Your body’s dead in that timeline, but [i]you[/i], Cyrus? You’re Justice’s enforcer. Time is merely a tool to the Arcanas, a little thing like death won’t get you out of this. 
The Judge: Each time you fail, time will rewind. Until you succeed. Aren’t you lucky?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Not the word I’d use.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: Come on, most mortals would KILL for infinite chances to get things right. Haha, get it?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: If you can control time itself, can’t you do more to help me?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: You think Prism is the only place on the brink of destruction?
The Judge: I’m already working nonstop managing the logistics of every enforcer, the last thing I need is you whining about the job [i]you[/i] signed up for.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I, I don’t even remember anything!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: You’ve got all the time in the world, I’m sure you’ll figure it out.
The Judge: Well, Cyrus, looks like our time is up. Try not to die so fast on this one.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Wait!!
 
<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: See you soon!

<<player_respawn YarnManager>>
===


title: FirstResurrection_Alt
---
<<set_portrait YarnManager Judge>>
The Judge: See you again soon~

<<player_respawn YarnManager>>
